The USING and USING NAMED clauses affect the WHERE clause, not the destination of updates. They are the update equivalents of FROM/FROM NAMED for the WHERE part.
[3.1.3 DELETE/INSERT](https://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#deleteInsert)

You can use `GRAPH` in an update:

```
INSERT { 
    GRAPH <http://example.org/> {
        ?ent a ex:Object
    }
} WHERE {
   ...
}
```

For the second part : 
The update has a `WITH`. It can't be mixed with using-graph-uri.
The spec of protocol says it's an error (not a Jena design decision)
https://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-protocol/#update-dataset

